[> Getting started
------------------
1. Install LiteX: https://github.com/enjoy-digital/litex/wiki/Installation

2. Set how many core you want
  export CPU_VARIANT=2c  (can be 1c, 2c, 4c, 8c)

3. Run the simulation:
  ./sim.py  --cpu-variant $CPU_VARIANT (--sdram-init to load the images) (--trace to enable waveform that will be located in build/gateware/dut.vcd)

4. Test on Hardware (Arty A7, up to 4c):
  ./arty.py --cpu-variant $CPU_VARIANT --uart-baudrate=1000000 --build --load
  lxterm --cpu-variant $CPU_VARIANT --images=images/images_$CPU_VARIANT.json /dev/ttyUSBX --speed=1000000 --no-crc
